def df_review(data):
    
    #     5   
    print('{0:^125}'.format('  '))
    display(data)
    print('-'*120)
    
    #     
    print('{0:^125}'.format('   '),end='\n\n')
    data.info()
    print('-'*120)
    
    #  -      
    print('{0:^125}'.format('         '))
    #  -             
    num_of_nan = data.isnull().sum().to_frame().reset_index().merge \
    (round(data.isnull().mean()*100,2).to_frame().reset_index(), on='index', how='left')
    #        -
    num_of_nan.columns = ['columns','nan_count','nan_ratio']
    num_of_nan['nan_ratio'] = num_of_nan['nan_ratio'].map('{0:.2f}%'.format)
    display(num_of_nan.sort_values(by='nan_count', ascending=False))
    print('-'*120)
    
    #  -      
    print(f'    : {data.duplicated().sum()}')
    print (f'    : {round(100*data.duplicated().sum()/data.shape[0],2)}%')
    print('-'*120,end='\n\n')
    
    #      
    print('{0:^125}'.format(' c   '))
    display(data.describe())

def street_extractor(row):
    
    #       ,     
    address = row['address'].split(',')
    
    #          
    lst = (
            ['', '.', '', '-', '', '.', '', '', '', '',  
             '', '', '', '', '', '-', '', '', 
             '', '', '- ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '']
           )
    
    #             
    for word in lst:
        for address_lst in address:
            #  ,    
            if word in address_lst: 
                return address_lst
    #   ,   'unknown'
    return ''
